Description

& SummaryAt PwC innovative and technological projects are our everyday life. As a consulting company, we have the advantage that we can work with clients from various industries around the world.
The company has 8 offices in Poland - Warsaw, Cracow, Katowice, Wroclaw, Gdansk, Poznan, Lublin, Lodz. Our Polish companies employ 6.500 people, including 1.500 people in technology teams. You can be one of us - join our community of solvers!

PwC’s Business Intelligence & Data Team is a dynamic team working on developing Business Intelligence tools, Data Warehousing, Process Mining and Data Analytics related solutions for both Polish and international clients, supporting them in the improvement of their decision making processes.

In this position you will be involved in Process Mining projects aiming at data-driven process analytics to help clients to optimize their operations and achieve business process excellence , with the responsibilities including, among others:
•... Delivery of complex Process Mining analysis, using cutting-edge technology (e.g. Celonis, Signavio, PowerBI) in a form of consulting project as well as on-site client implementation;
• Development of analytical tools for enabling powerful data-driven process analysis (data visualization);
• Analysis of data sources (eg. transactional databases like SAP) to identify data scope for process model and eventlog design;
• Data transformation and modelling aiming at process data model development incl. eventlog using mostly SQL;
• Conducting analysis to identify process inefficiencies, bottlenecks and pain points in order to draw conclusions and develop process improvements recommendations;
• Helping in management and delivery of large scale projects.

We are looking for the candidates experienced in a couple of the following areas:
• General understanding of Process Mining concept;
• Knowledge of leading commercial or academic Process Mining technologies would be an advantage (e.g. Celonis, Signavio, PAFnow, Disco, Prom, process.science);
• Knowledge of leading data visualisation technologies would be an advantage (e.g. PowerBI, Qlik Sense, Tableau);
• Knowledge of data querying technologies (e.g. SQL);
• Understanding of data modelling principles, databases and ETL solutions;
• Following candidates characteristic would also be an advantage:

Knowledge of core SAP FICO tables;

Knowledge of key ERP systems structure and infrastructure;

Experience in areas: process optimization, process consulting, process mining, process mapping, process transformation;
• Strong interpersonal and communication skills - necessary in everyday cooperation with clients and international teams;
• Ability to solve complex problems;
• Excellent written and verbal communication skills – in Polish and English.

By joining us you gain:
• work flexibility - openness for your preferences regarding contract form (B2B or employment contract), hybrid working model, flexible start of the day, workation, sabbatical leave and additional summer solutions (e.g. Slow Fridays),
• development and upskilling - our full support during onboarding process, mentoring from experienced colleagues, training sessions, workshops, certification co/financed by PwC e.g. Microsoft and Celonis and conversations with native speaker,
• wide medical and wellbeing program - medical care package (incl. dental care, freedom of treatment, physiotherapy), various insurance packages (incl. foreign travel insurance), coaching, psychological consultations, concierge for young parents, sports groups and more,
• access to an online cafeteria where you may find i.a. vouchers (e.g. Zalando, Ikea, Allegro, Frisco), discounts for IT devices (e.g. Apple, Lenovo, Orange) and car purchase, Multisport card,
• 3 paid hours for volunteering per month,
• and when you start enjoying PwC as much as we do, you may get a financial bonus in exchange for recommending your friend to work with us.

Send your application today! In case you have any additional questions, contact us: <

